================================================================================
  DATABASE SCHEMA
================================================================================

Tables: 3
  [1] suppliers (5 rows with sample data)
      - id (PK), supplier_id (UNIQUE), name, email, phone
      - address, city, state, zip_code, country
      - category, status, created_at, updated_at

  [2] products (10 rows with sample data)
      - id (PK), supplier_id (FK), product_code (UNIQUE)
      - product_name, description, unit_cost
      - lead_time_days, min_order_qty, created_at

  [3] search_history (2 rows from testing)
      - id (PK), search_query, results_count
      - user_id, created_at

Indexes: 4
  [1] idx_supplier_name - Fast full-text search
  [2] idx_supplier_category - Fast category filtering
  [3] idx_product_supplier - Fast product lookup
  [4] idx_search_history_date - Fast analytics queries

Constraints:
  - UNIQUE: suppliers.supplier_id, products.product_code
  - FOREIGN KEY: products.supplier_id -> suppliers.id (CASCADE DELETE)
  - CHECK: suppliers.status IN ('active', 'inactive', 'pending')
  - AUTOINCREMENT: All primary keys
  - DEFAULT: Timestamps (CURRENT_TIMESTAMP), status='active'

